Responsible for developing and maintaining software applications and systems that support the Identity and Access Management (IAM) team. Collaborate with other software engineers, product managers, and stakeholders to design and implement new features and functionality. Troubleshoot and resolve issues related to software applications and systems. Leverage web technologies such as ASP.NET, Web APIs, and RESTful services to create dynamic and responsive solutions. Write and maintain technical documentation related to software applications and systems.



Employed will accept a Master's degree in Computer Science or related field. Position requires:  



1\. Algorithms, data structures, and software development methodologies;  

2\. Java, C\#, Python, or C\+\+ with the ability to write clean, efficient, and well\-documented code;  

3\. Software development tools, including VS Code, Microsoft visual Studio, or Eclipse;  

4\. Designing and implementing RESTful Web APIs using .NET C\# or Java;  

5\. SQL and NoSQL databases, design, query, and maintain databases;  

6\. Cloud platforms, including AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud;  

7\. Unit testing principles and writing and executing unit tests;  

8\. Git for source code management;  

9\. Working in Agile development environments and Scrum methodologies.


